// Secrets.xcconfig.example  —  BRING-YOUR-OWN-KEY template (NO real secrets live here)
// =====================================================================================
// This is a TEMPLATE for the NEW minimal-realtime-kit repo. It contains ZERO real keys.
//
// Copy it to a GITIGNORED real file and paste YOUR OWN values:
//     cp Config/Secrets.xcconfig.example Config/Secrets.xcconfig
//
// Then have your base build config pull it in (a committed Config/Base.xcconfig can do:
//     #include? "Secrets.xcconfig"
// so a fresh clone with no Secrets.xcconfig still compiles — the `?` makes it optional).
//
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Pick ONE auth transport (see research/05-config-keys-build.md + research/07 BYOK notes):
//
//   A) Direct BYO OpenAI key — simplest; the real key sits on-device (fine for local/dev,
//      NOT recommended for a shipped app):
//          OPENAI_API_KEY = <<PASTE_YOUR_OWN>>
//
//   B) Via AIProxy — keeps the real OpenAI key OFF-device. You paste a *partial* key + a
//      service URL from YOUR OWN AIProxy dashboard (these are NOT the OpenAI key):
//          AIPROXY_PARTIAL_KEY = <<PASTE_YOUR_OWN>>
//          AIPROXY_SERVICE_URL = <<PASTE_YOUR_OWN>>
//      Simulator-only DeviceCheck bypass (the sim can't make DeviceCheck tokens; never ships):
//          AIPROXY_DEVICE_CHECK_BYPASS = <<PASTE_YOUR_OWN>>
//
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// GOTCHA: xcconfig build settings are NOT visible to Swift at runtime by themselves.
// To read one in code, surface it through the generated Info.plist. In your target's
// build settings (or a committed base .xcconfig) add, for each value you need at runtime:
//     INFOPLIST_KEY_OPENAI_API_KEY = $(OPENAI_API_KEY)
// then read it via Bundle.main.object(forInfoDictionaryKey: "OPENAI_API_KEY").
// See SecretsReader.swift.example. (Verify the INFOPLIST_KEY_ mapping when you build —
// it's the one medium-confidence step in this plan; an in-app paste-to-Keychain flow
// avoids the plumbing entirely and is the cleaner option for an open-source app.)
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

// Defaults are intentionally EMPTY so a fresh clone (no Secrets.xcconfig) still compiles.
OPENAI_API_KEY =
AIPROXY_PARTIAL_KEY =
AIPROXY_SERVICE_URL =
AIPROXY_DEVICE_CHECK_BYPASS =
